               <msContents>
                  <summary>The undated third volume of a complete set of the <title>Rawz̤at al-Ṣafā</title> (Garden of Purity), a general history from the creation of the world to the time of the author, together
                     with <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_14603"
                        ><idno>Persian MS 387</idno></ref>, <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_14604"
                           >388</ref>, <ref
                              target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6887">390</ref>, 
                     <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6888">391</ref>, <ref
                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6889">392</ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6890">393</ref>, and <ref
                              target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6891">394</ref>. While uniformly bound, the variant dimensions, formats and colophons within the set suggest that former owner George William Hamilton (1807–1868) assembled it together from disparate volumes completed in various locations and at different times.
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="manuscript_14605-item1">
                     <author key="person_175393012" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/175393012/" change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Mīr Khvānd, Muḥammad ibn Khāvandshāh, 1433-1498</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">مير خواند، محمد بن خواندشاه</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_273" change="#ids-cleanup">Rawz̤at al-Ṣafāʼ fī Sīrat al-Anbiyā wa-al-Mulūk</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_273" change="#ids-cleanup">Rawḍat al-Ṣafāʼ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_273" change="#ids-cleanup">روضة الصفاء فی سیرة الانبيا و الملوك</title>
                                       <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents><physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
